What is your biggest challenge as a univ:
As a university student, my biggest challenges are:

Limited access to learning resources and internet at my university, which makes studying more difficult.

Balancing academic studies with leadership and future goals, since I am also active in youth organization work and planning for my long-term dreams.

Improving my English skills (especially writing and vocabulary), which is important for scholarships and international opportunities.

Financial limitations and family expectations, which add extra pressure to succeed.

Having many interests (such as cybersecurity, app development, and leadership) but needing to stay focused on one area at a time.
What resources would help reduce your st: Having better access to the internet and quality learning resources would really help me. Guidance from mentors or teachers, as well as support to improve my English skills, would also reduce a lot of stress. Financial aid or scholarships could ease family pressure, and having a good study environment or useful digital tools would make learning much easier.
